        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7105970?u=89742e942b73152c9fdd230b6eedf096a71e58b7&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><p dir=\"auto\">List of changes proposed in this PR:</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\">This pull request aims to add Firefox relay to the email aliasing page.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\">I do use Firefox relay and I am a premium user</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"auto\">There have been some talk about adding it</p>\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://discuss.privacyguides.net/t/add-mozilla-relay-to-aliasing-services/22638\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://discuss.privacyguides.net/t/add-mozilla-relay-to-aliasing-services/22638</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p dir=\"auto\"><a href=\"https://discuss.privacyguides.net/t/can-firefox-relay-be-trusted/15800\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://discuss.privacyguides.net/t/can-firefox-relay-be-trusted/15800</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Thoughts?</p>",
            "url": "https://github.com/privacyguides/privacyguides.org/pull/3070",
            "title": "update!: Add Firefox Relay",
            "date_modified": "2025-09-12T06:03:58.000Z",
            "date_published": "2025-07-02T16:15:44.000Z",
            "author": {
