            "date_published": "2025-06-25T08:01:35.000Z",
            "author": {
                "name": "sawaraken",
                "url": "https://github.com/apps/sawaraken"
            }
        },
        {
            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/837136?u=73b5c34325606e447be7074fd0deefc55a004c82&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/><p dir=\"auto\">I've received a pingback from <a href=\"https://brid.gy/comment/mastodon/@edent@mastodon.social/110151657347210229/110151774995722710\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://brid.gy/comment/mastodon/@edent@mastodon.social/110151657347210229/110151774995722710</a></p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The plugin gets the author's name, URL, avatar, and text content. It doesn't include the image along with the post.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">Sometimes, people reply with <em>only</em> an image. Or their reply references an attached image. It would be useful to include this as part of the webmention.</p>\n<p dir=\"auto\">The HTML code is:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-text-html-basic notranslate position-relative overflow-auto\" dir=\"auto\" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content=\"&lt;span class=&quot;p-author h-card&quot;&gt;\n   &lt;a class=&quot;p-name u-url&quot; href=&quot;https://mastodon.social/@Edent&quot;&gt;Terence Eden&lt;/a&gt;\n   &lt;a class=&quot;u-url&quot; href=&quot;https://edent.tel/&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\n   &lt;a class=&quot;u-url&quot; href=&quot;https://shkspr.mobi/blog&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;\n   &lt;span class=&quot;p-nickname&quot;&gt;Edent&lt;/span&gt;\n   &lt;img class=&quot;u-photo&quot; src=&quot;https://files.mastodon.social/accounts/avatars/000/007/112/original/37df032a5951b96c.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;\n&lt;a title=&quot;mastodon.social/@Edent/110151774995722710&quot; class=&quot;u-url&quot; href=&quot;https://mastodon.social/@Edent/110151774995722710&quot;&gt;mastodon.social/@Edent/1101517...&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;div class=&quot;e-content p-name&quot;&gt;\n   &lt;p&gt;Incidentally, this was my favourite comment when I announced I was doing an MSc.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The rage it induced powered me through many a tutorial!&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;img class=&quot;